cv_explanation = "In the investing world, the coefficient of variation allows you to determine how much volatility, or " \
                 "risk, you are assuming in comparison to the amount of return you can expect from your investment. " \
                 "In simple language, the lower the ratio of standard deviation to mean return, the better your " \
                 "risk-return tradeoff. Note that if the expected return in the denominator of the calculation is " \
                "negative or zero, the coefficient of variation could be misleading."